{% raw %}<h2>The Problem</h2>

<p>The web platform provides substantial i18n primitives through the <code>Intl</code> API &mdash; number formatting, date formatting, plural rules, collation, segmentation, and more. But major frameworks ship significant i18n libraries on top of these standards because critical capabilities are missing. This research maps the gap between what web standards provide and what frameworks deliver, identifying what Web Everything should adopt.</p>


<h2>What Web Standards Already Provide</h2>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>API</th><th>Status</th><th>What It Does</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.NumberFormat</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>Locale-aware number, currency, and unit formatting</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.DateTimeFormat</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>Locale-aware date and time formatting</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.RelativeTimeFormat</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>Relative time ("2 days ago")</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.PluralRules</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>Plural category for a number (one, few, many, other)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.ListFormat</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>List formatting ("A, B, and C")</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.Segmenter</code></td><td>Baseline 2024</td><td>Text segmentation (graphemes, words, sentences)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.DisplayNames</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>Localized names for languages, regions, currencies</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Intl.Locale</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>Locale string parsing and negotiation</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>navigator.languages</code></td><td>Baseline</td><td>User's preferred languages</td></tr>
    <tr><td>CSS Logical Properties</td><td>Baseline</td><td>Direction-agnostic layout (<code>margin-inline-start</code>)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>dir</code> attribute</td><td>Baseline</td><td>Text direction (LTR/RTL)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>:dir()</code> pseudo-class</td><td>Baseline 2023</td><td>Style based on text direction</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>translate</code> attribute</td><td>Baseline</td><td>Mark content for translation tools</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>lang</code> attribute</td><td>Baseline</td><td>Declare content language</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>The standards are strong for formatting individual values.</strong> The gaps are in <em>composing messages</em>, <em>managing translations</em>, and <em>reactive locale switching</em>.</p>


