<h2>Gap Analysis: What Frameworks Provide That Standards Do Not</h2>

<h3>Critical Gaps</h3>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Web Standard</th><th>Framework Solutions</th><th>Adoption Path for WE</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Message formatting with variables</strong></td>
      <td><code>Intl.MessageFormat</code> (TC39 Stage 1)</td>
      <td>ICU MessageFormat (FormatJS, vue-i18n, ember-intl), i18next interpolation, Fluent</td>
      <td>Message formatter block using MF2 syntax; polyfill until standard ships</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Variable interpolation</strong></td>
      <td>None</td>
      <td>All frameworks &mdash; <code>{name}</code>, <code>{{name}}</code>, tagged templates</td>
      <td>Built into message formatter</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Fallback locale chains</strong></td>
      <td>None</td>
      <td>All frameworks &mdash; <code>fr-CA</code> &rarr; <code>fr</code> &rarr; <code>en</code></td>
      <td>Message resolver walks chain; configurable via injector</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Dynamic locale switching</strong></td>
      <td>None (lang attribute has no reactive effect)</td>
      <td>All runtime frameworks &mdash; reactive state triggers re-render</td>
      <td>Locale store (<code>CustomStore</code>) + reactive <code>@t</code> context</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

